16 WHEREAS, the western region of Georgia is currently experiencing a heightened outbreak
17 of the southern pine beetle, resulting in extensive damage to pine stands and threatening the
18 sustainability of the state's forest resources; and
19 WHEREAS, the Georgia Forestry Commission has provided critical guidance and resources
20 to landowners to implement sound forestry practices that reduce the risk of infestation by the
21 southern pine beetle and improve overall forest resilience; and
22 WHEREAS, thinning overcrowded stands, removing infested trees, and adhering to best
23 management practices are the most effective means of controlling and preventing further
24 spread of the southern pine beetle.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
26 the members of this body:
27 (1) Recognize the significant threat posed by the southern pine beetle to Georgia's
28 forests;
29 (2) Recognize the acute and ongoing challenge of the southern pine beetle outbreak in
30 the western region of this state; and
31 (3) Encourage Georgia landowners to take all steps necessary to mitigate the spread of
32 this outbreak through proper forest management and adherence to best management
33 practices outlined by the Georgia Forestry Commission.
34 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
35 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
36 public and the press.
